    <item>
      <title>Optical Illusions with ShaderToy</title>
      <link>/post/optical-illusions/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 18 Apr 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/post/optical-illusions/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Yesterday I was waiting for one of my PT frames to finish, viewing the latest contributions in &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.shadertoy.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Shadertoy&lt;/a&gt;, when I hitted one shader about &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.shadertoy.com/view/4dcfzr&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;optical illusions&lt;/a&gt; so I decided to made one on my own.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was the result&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;iframe width=&#34;640&#34; height=&#34;360&#34; frameborder=&#34;0&#34; src=&#34;https://www.shadertoy.com/embed/XddfRr?gui=true&amp;t=10&amp;paused=true&amp;muted=false&#34; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which I managed to made in 97 chars, although &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.shadertoy.com/user/FabriceNeyret2&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;FabriceNeyret2&lt;/a&gt; came to made it in 60 chars (thanks for the comments and help in all the shaders).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After making the Hermann Grid I made 4 more illusions, being the &lt;em&gt;Induced Contrast Asynchrony&lt;/em&gt; my favourite. I have included highlights to all of them in this page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;iframe width=&#34;640&#34; height=&#34;360&#34; frameborder=&#34;0&#34; src=&#34;https://www.shadertoy.com/embed/XsdfRH?gui=true&amp;t=10&amp;paused=false&amp;muted=false&#34; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;

